===Alternative spelling===
*[[homalographic]]
===Adjective===
'''homolographic'''

#{{cartography}} Describing a [[map]] with the property of being equal-area; thus a circle of the constant [[radius]], located anywhere on the map, covers the same area on the mapped surface.  Also called equivalent, [[authalic]], [[equiareal]].

*The most commonly used term for this property is equal-area.